This paper deals with a stochastic submodular maximization problem, which involves optimization and probability theory. The problem also involves budget constraints and decision-making, which are common topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). However, the paper also involves machine learning (cs.AI), optimization (cs.LG), game theory (cs.GT), and information theory (cs.IT) concepts, which are all relevant to the problem.
